responses.question2: It's essential to be able to learn what is happening by looking at the video and seeing what parts of the data means what. It also can show you what is happening, and when to annotate.
responses.question3: It's essential to have a raw data. Like a sound or a wave length that will signify what is happening.
responses.question4: It's important to use the video as a tool in order to learn what the data represents. Honestly, I like the video better because I didn't have to second guess myself on things.
